question:
\begin{gather*}
\int_{-100}^{-10} \left( \frac{x^2 - x}{x^3 - 3x + 1} \right)^2\,dx + \\
\int_{\frac{1}{101}}^{\frac{1}{11}} \left( \frac{x^2 - x}{x^3 - 3x + 1} \right)^2\,dx + \\
\int_{\frac{101}{100}}^{\frac{11}{10}} \left( \frac{x^2 - x}{x^3 - 3x + 1} \right)^2\,dx
\end{gather*}
is a rational number.

